description:
11th Hour Recordings is back with ‚ÄòEndless Days‚Äô, our most dancefloor excursion so far - 4 slamming new techno and electro cuts, starting with the outrageously tough beat and grinding basslines of ‚ÄòKick It‚Äô, followed by a stunning high-tech-funk remake by Motech main man and UR assault squad member DJ 3000; who takes the heavy bass of the original and layers on new jazzed out synth hooks and stripped down percussion.
On the flip, ‚ÄòCold Restraint‚Äô is a straight out dancefloor bomb - tough driving percussion threaded with a distorted bleep hook and searing strings, all pushed forward by one of the nastiest basslines around; whilst ‚ÄòDown and Out in EC2‚Ä≤ provides a deep, driving and endlessly shiftingelectro workout.

This release is already getting rave reviews from press and public worldwide, with DJ magazine making it ‚ÄòElectro single of the month‚Äô Feb 09 and Update naming it ‚ÄòEssential single of the month‚Äô, as well as featuring in M8, Fact, Mixmag and many others. It is getting strong DJ support from Laurent Garnier,UR, Fabrice Lig, Mark Broom and many more‚Ä¶
title: Matt Chester - Endless Days EP (ehr006)

description:
DC shows with his full 12" debut an outstanding spectrum of his talent. Side A contains deep and heavy bass sounds paired with an itching synthline. To say it in a few words, turn your speakers on and get ready to freak out. "Vertical Output" is definitely the uptempo cracker on this record! 

Side B comes with some different styles. "Yorktown Recreation" and "Chocolate Milk" are pure delight! Microkorg extravaganza up to the sky, confused funk chords backed by insane jazz lines. These two bangers are arranged in the typical Dorian Concept manner and give a pretty good insight of his sound universe. Maximized Minimalization - Headphone Music for the Dancefloor!

Tracklisting:
01. Dorian Concept - Vertical Output
02. Dorian Concept - Yorktown Recreation
03. Dorian Concept - Chocolate Milk

description:
Tilman Ehrhorn "Past Utopia" is out January 28, 2011 on Neo Ouija. 

Tilman's debut album "Task", influenced by other contemporary electronic artists as well as his background in jazz music, was released on the Mille Plateaux label. On his sophomore album *Heading For The Open Spaces* he turned towards a more or less characteristic ambient sound, working with calm tracks, sounds and atmospheres, that are nevertheless inspired by the funkyness of 70ÃÅs jazzrock music. The manufacturing process of his newest album "Past Utopia" is still based on sample work and software but besides the virtual sound design, instruments like vintage analogue synthesizers and electric guitars are used as a source of sound. Most of the tracks on "Past Utopia" are musically inspired through British Pop Music. The beginning of the Psychedelic/Progessive Rock era of the late sixtie≈õs, including groups lush as Pink Floyd, Genesis, Tomorrow and Yes might be as well a big influence as conceptional productions of the early and mid-eighties, like Frankie Goes To Hollywood, Depeche Mode and Talk Talk. Therefore the idea behind "Past Utopia" is to introduce music that doesn't fit into the stereotypical attributes of electronic music. Instead, Tilman has crafted abstract and modified instrumental pop songs that combine the spirit of different musical epochs with an individual idea of electronic music.
tag_list: "mille plateaux" resopal "neo ouija" jazz krautrock "nord modular" ehrhorn ctm idm warm shoegaze
title: Tilman Ehrhorn - Past Utopia

description:
A circle of friends. A shabby rehearsal room. A band called JSBL and their debut.

Opener ‚ÄúThe Flu‚Äù, is great listening material with the potential to make you dance your shoes off. The best pair even! On the other hand ‚ÄúDer Mann mit den Schwankungen‚Äù (‚ÄúThe Man with the Fluctuations‚Äù), is a track that slowly but surely evolves into a monumental Jazz-rock hybrid.

Next is ‚ÄúJimbo‚Äù, a razor-sharp, uptempo, instrumental broken power load with a mind-blowing key solo. This guy must feel like he‚Äôs on an infinite roller coaster ride on the JSBL claviature. ‚ÄúRekindle of the Libido‚Äù starts off with a Contemporary Flow Bop and ends in a dramatic Cyberfunk Orgy. Thematically not far away is ‚ÄúFooled by Needs‚Äù. A gigantic bassline interacts with synth, drums and guitar to produce acoustic pleasure of the third kind. Full spectrum annihilation! Weird psychedelic 70s atmosphere is what best describes ‚ÄúParental Square ¬¥79‚Äù. This bizarre sneaker brings ‚ÄúTwice Upon Two Times‚Äù to a gentle close. Gentle and a little bamboozled.

Tracklisting:
01. JSBL - The Flu
02. JSBL - Der Mann mit den Schwankungen
03. JSBL - Jimbo
04. JSBL - Rekindle of the Libido
05. JSBL - Fooled by Needs
06. JSBL - Parental Square ¬¥79

description:
Uriel is Raskolnikov's Dream first album.

Raskolnikov's Dream is a melodic electronica project from Greece. Thus far, there has been only one album, Uriel, which you can buy from the official site. The pieces are a mixture of ambient, IDM, synth-pop and my own special taste :)

You can find more about Raskolnikov's Dream and listen and buy the WHOLE album at the official site at http://raskolnikovsdream.com

Furthermore, Raskolnikov's Dream is the creator of two more sites.

The first one is http://musikality.net, a site for independent musicians, with tutorials and articles on various subjects, like music theory, software and promotion.

The other one is http://encefalus.com, a psychology site with analyses on various subjects.

Please leave comments and feedback at raskolnikov@raskolnikovsdream.com

description:
mit sprog aka bertrand lacroix betritt wba zum ersten mal internationale gefilde. der aus nantes stammende 30 j√§hrige gibt mit ‚Äûall is blue‚Äú sein debut auf wba. charakterisiert wird sein minimaler treibender sound durch verspielte elemente mit wechselnden percussions.
schon mit 12 jahren wurde sein heutiger weg gepr√§gt. durch die zahlreiche plattensammlung seines vaters, der vor allem songs aus den bereichen swing, jazz oder beebop besass wurde sein interesse f√ºr musik geweckt. nach anf√§nglichen vorlieben f√ºr acid house und hiphop gelangte er √ºber techno und breakbeat im jahr 2005 zu minimalmusik. seit 2007 produziert er minimalsound und ist neben seinem eigenen recordshop ‚Äûbug 909‚Äú auch als liveact in europa unterwegs.

- - - - - - - - - - 

it‚Äôs the first time that wba enters the international stage with french guy sprog aka bertrand lacroix. ‚Äûall is blue‚Äú ist the debut of the 30 year old guy from nantes on wba. the enormous record collection of his father which contains mostly swing, jazz and beebop was his first contct with music as a 12 year old boy and later his biggest inluence.
first he tried acid house and hip hop, than he changed to techno and breakbeat and finally to minimal in 2005. for almost 2 years he is producing and also touring in europe with his own live act when he has time because his own record shop ‚Äûbug 909‚Äú needs his full attention.
sprogs own sound is chracterized by driving minimal and tricky elements with changing percussions.
title: wba011 - sprog - all is blue

description:
After a long hiatus, Jeff Danos aka TESTUBE returns from
      the outer limits of electro with the Covert EP, an intriguing
      approach at vocal-driven "experimental pop". Inspired by
      classic post-punk and dream pop flavors, as well as edgy
      contemporary electroclashers like The Faint and Goldfrapp,
      the act's new EP is the second release made available by the
      recently formed independent label GLIM RECORDS.
      
      Intermittently composting abstract rhythms and industrial 
      glitch sampling into a slightly more accessible framework of 
      dark electro-pop, the Covert EP serves as an appropriate
      teaser for an upcoming TESTUBE full length in 2009.
      
      More info here: http://testube.com/covert
tag_list: industrial ebm shoegaze electroclash idm dreampop shoegazer "electro clash" post-industrial "experimental pop" "new wave" alt-pop
title: Covert EP

description:
Spherical Journey

Toni Polkowski and Danny Prusseit founded in 2001 the project Atmogat. Now in the beginning of 2009 there going to surprise us with an EP which sounds surprisingly emanzipated.

It's a five tracker EP, and with a runtime from 30 minutes a work by its own Saluta, the first track is a shuffled moody track, which inaugurates us into the soundcosmos of Atmogat. Springtime, the second track works with a vocal piece. The track get thus a techy attitude, which fits absolutely in to the concept of the EP. Neutron Bionic comes along with a repetitive warp and a haunting spherical sound in the background. It's the most powerful track on the EP and should be heard for sure. Esguman and Bianconic, the last both tracks are quite good and are fitting into the EP perfectly as well. In its own, the Neutro Bionic EP is a solid piece of work where you can hear the leitmotif on every track. If you take the journey you don√¢t have to buckle up because it√¢s a slow ride but interesting anyway. Good Work!
[Cornelis Clement]
title: cl-021 | Atmogat - Neutro Bionic EP

description:
A whole year has passed since our last¬†all rounder package,¬†Cup Of Chi, yet again we bring to your door a selection of goodies, this time a careful mixture of beats, cuts, glitches, and just a bit of pepper. AMB's "Rust" has been hammering the breakbeat floors for some time now, which is followed by the massive Fine Cut Bodies¬†techhouse rework of "Be Infected" (original by the Hungarian vocalist, Varga Zsuzsa). The closing piece is brought to you by the Hungarian glitch maistro: Kodek, who has prepared a deep melancholic downtempo for the colder winter nights.
Already gaining support from the likes of Santiago+Bushido, Jody Wisternoff, Laurent Garnier, Kevin Beber, Mylo, Mr No Hands, Nick Supply, Tamsin, Murray Richardson, Presslaboys, Jay Cunning, General Midi, JDS, Dov, FreQ Nasty, etc...

description:
THIS IS THE DIGITAL VERSION OF THIS EP (also available as a 2 tracks Vinyl Sampler)
        BUY DIRECTLY ON PRIMARY DIGITAL SHOPS
      HERE :  http://roomwav.com/site/2009/03/viewed001-va-perspectives-01
                    
        We are proud to present you our very first release coming as part of the seasonal serie PERSPECTIVES which will introduce you to some core artists of our roster through exclusive tracks & samples of our forthcoming releases. PERSPECTIVES 01 kicks off in style with a very unexpected track by Deep House veteran ABACUS, known for his classics on Chicago‚Äòs Guidance in the 90‚Äòs. This dark & dubby rollercoaster has been in our dj sets for a long time and it has confi rmed many times to be an outstanding track judging by crowds reactions. Crossing the lines between House & Techno territories, it represents proudly our label‚Äòs motto‚Ä¶
                      
                      For the ones that witnessed already smoky & dirty intimate clubs back in the days, this one is for you : German sound wizard MARLOW, known for releases on Moon Harbour, Konsequenz & soon on Dennis Ferrer‚Äòs Objektivity, offer you Fonk, a raw moody House odyssey loaded of Jazz & Funk samples carrying an early House vibe reminiscent of Lil‚Äò Louis & the Detroit school of Kenny Dixon Jr. Perfect to set up a special climax on the floors‚Ä¶ A retro futuristic approach is also displayed in the rumbling Bass-Ment Tale by label honcho Dairmount & his partner in crime Marino Berardi, noticed for his early releases on Ovum & Wave Music some years back. DAIRMOUNT & BERARDI deliberately wanted to bring their own persperctive on Hip Hop esthetics once pioneered by people such as DJ Duke, Pal Joey or Kenny Dope. House music as you don‚Äòt hear very often anymore‚Ä¶
                      
                      The next 2 tracks are belonging to some of our forthcoming releases and we couldn‚Äòt wait to share them with you as a promise of things to come : Jazzanova‚Äòs own Roskow has ‚Äûcooked‚Äú a wonderful EP for the label under his solo moniker SYGAIRE and we are uncovering here the blasting Deep House remix of The Time Is Now by SHUR-I-KAN, known for his work on Freerange & Urbantorque to name a few. Closing this EP with class & distinction, Moodmusic‚Äòs head SASSE has reworked in a late night groover mode the long awaited Subakuatik Blues by PETTER & DAIRMOUNT, due early may in its original glory with an extra Sasse‚Äòs dub & a fantastic Russ Gabriel rework.
                      A well rounded first episode selected for you by DAIRMOUNT.
                      
                      SELECTED DJ FEEDBACKS:
                      
                          * ‚ÄûWow! what a debut! splendid bunch of tracks here‚Ä¶‚Äú - JIMPSTER [Freerange]
                          * ‚ÄûAbsolutely classic!‚Äú - OSUNLADE [Yoruba]
                          * ‚Äú I am totally in love with Brethren! I promise I will buy the vinyl‚Ä¶‚Äú - DARKO ESSER [Wolfskuil records)]
                          * ‚ÄúFantastic EP. loving The Answer, Shur-I-Kan mix and the Brethren track - top notch!‚Äú - SEI A [Sole Music, Missive]
                          * ‚ÄúThe answer is amazing!!! mega deep bomb!‚Äú - KONRAD BLACK [M_nus, Wagon Repair]
                          * ‚ÄûGreat ep! Really love this a lot full support from me‚Äú - LAURENT GARNIER [F Com]
                          * ‚ÄûJust plain wicked! All trax are just brilliant. There just all so good!!‚Äú - BROTHERS VIBE [Mixx records]
                          * ‚ÄûThe Abacus track is amazing, I definitely need a 12‚Äú!‚Äú - MANUEL TUR [Freerange]
                          * ‚Äû Love the whole package! Will fit perfectly in my sets. Big up!‚Äú - MOTOR CITY DRUM ENSEMBLE [2020 Vision, Quintessentials]
                          * ‚ÄúNothing short of stellar dancefloor material here! all trax going in my DJ bag. WOW!‚Äú - BRENDON MOELLER [Connaisseur, Echochord]
                          * ‚ÄúThis is too good to decide which one to pick‚Ä¶Heavy, edgy, right up my street‚Äú - RAINER TR√úBY
                          * ‚ÄúThis much class out of a new label‚Ä¶ Totally awesome.‚Äú - ATJAZZ
                          * ‚ÄûSolid EP with nuff tunes 2 choose from‚Ä¶ Especially feelin‚Äò Bass-Ment Tale‚Äú - MAD MATS [Raw Fusion]
                          * ‚ÄûVery nice music selection indeed! I love the tracks‚Äú - ALEX KID [Imprim√©, Cadenza, Rekids]
                          * ‚ÄûThe Answer is the shizzy!‚Äú - STACEY PULLEN [Blak Flag]
                          * ‚ÄûAwesome! Hard to pick a favourite. Shurikan‚Äòs mix is really amazing and the Bass-Ment is also a hot contender‚Ä¶‚Äú - RUSS GABRIEL [Mobilee, Ferox]
                          * ‚ÄûVery good package of traxx..lot‚Äòs of good ideas in there 4 sure‚Äú - CHARLES WEBSTER [Miso, Defected]
                          * ‚ÄûGreat package here. Plenty of shit to like. The Abacus track is a slammer for sure. Also diggin the Bass-Ment Tale and Sasse stringity deepness.‚Äú - PHONOGENIC [Cocoon, Moodmusic]
                          * ‚ÄúHard to choose a favourite as all the tracks are good! Full support!‚Äú - FABRICE LIG [Third Ear, Versatile]
                          * ‚ÄúGreat release! Will play this for sure‚Ä¶‚Äú - PETER KRUDER [G-Stone, Compost]
                          * ‚ÄúWhat an outstanding first release on RWAV‚Ä¶ Quality dirty house music that pushes the boundaries‚Äú - SKI OAKENFUL [BBE, Primaudial]
                      
                          * Also loved & supported by Tiefschwarz, Gerd, Audiofly, Mad Mats, Dixon, Dj Hell, Kiko Navarro, Djulz, Technasia, Nick Holder, Slam, Estroe, Joris Voorn, Tiger Stripes, Milton Jackson, Mazi, Domu, Chicken Lips, Lovebirds, Afrilounge, Ken Ishi‚Ä¶

description:
Percute is a deep and percussive house track, bringing lush chords, warm throbbing bass sounds into a perfect warm up track.
    Inconscience is a floor filling gem of a track, looping insanely into a dominating crescendo that invites any crowd to raise their hands. Minimal techno at its best! 
    Travel is more like an artist track, a fusion of blending futuristic house, with a perfect harmony and groove, a summer gem which got most of the attention so far ...
    
    
    
    
    
    DJ Support: Laurent Garnier, Lee Burridge, Fra Soler, Sasha, Sebastian Roya, Deep Mariano, Hernan Cattaneo, John Digweed, Behrouz, Peter Kruder, Mazi ,Carl Cox,etc.
title: Snejl005 - Ludovic Vendi - Inconscience EP

description:
SNEJL is back now with its 6th instalment, this time coming from a rising talent out of  Germany . After growing up with hardcore-techno that was going over to a "90s-techno-allround-interest", Dinamoe  - by his real name Rico Puestel ‚Äì started to produce his own sound, ending up with releases under Minisketch, Tanzbar, 9Volt and more ‚Ä¶ His debut on SNEJL is showcasing his brilliant talent and vision for future underground music , which we describe it as DARK, SOULFUL TECHNO at its best!
    
    
    Dj support : Sasha, Laurent Garnier, Remute, Fra Soler, Mijk van Dijk, Markus Guentner, Alland Byallo, Christian Sol, Xpansul, Anthony Pappa, Dario Zenker, Tim Green
title: Snejl006 - Dinamoe - Lifeline EP

description:
RETROCHINE - FROM THE PRODUCERS OF 5 TIME PLATINUM SELLING CD "SHANGHAI LOUNGE DIVAS VOL.1" PRESENT THE NEW CD ALBUM "RETROCHINE"
      
      THE STORY SO FAR . . .
      RETROCHINE is the second Schtung Music release celebrating Chinese pop music from a bygone era with a 21st Century twist. The first was ‚ÄòPathe 100 ‚Äì The Shanghai Divas Redefined (Vol. I)‚Äô released in 2003. 
      Producers Ian Widgery and Morton Wilson have reunited to partner with Celestial Pictures Ltd. in paying tribute to soundtracks from Shaw Brothers movies shot in Hong Kong during the late 50s and early 60s. 
      
      IAN WIDGERY
      U.K. Composer / Producer Ian Widgery emerged as a highly sought after Remix Artiste & DJ in the London dance scene during the 1990s, collaborating with both major and independent record labels. His tracks have been played on dance floors around the globe by Pete Tong, Sasha, Paul Oakenfold and Tiesto. 
      
      Now, 70 releases later, Widgery has gained recognition as part of the new wave of global producers. Working from his Vancouver studio, Like Music Productions, he has a clear mission to produce cutting edge tracks that transcend musical genres. He owns a LOT of vintage analog gear.
       myspace.com/ianwidgery  
      
      MORTON WILSON
      Morton Wilson has spent the last 25 years in Hong Kong cloistered in Schtung Music‚Äôs landmark Kennedy Road studios. He works with a select group of composers, arrangers and artistes from Hong Kong, Singapore, Shanghai, Beijing, Bombay and a few other exotic locations. 
       Schtung Music,  Hong Kong  
      
       
      RETROCHINE
      With post war changes in China the curtain had been firmly drawn on Shanghai‚Äôs glorious and decadent era as ‚ÄòParis of the East‚Äô. The nightclubs were closed, movie studios were turning out ‚Äòpatriotic‚Äô films and the stars of the silver screen had all long since sailed away.
      Cut to Hong Kong, 1957: A young filmmaker named Run Run Shaw purchased 46 acres of land on a quiet hilltop in Clearwater Bay overlooking the South China Sea. His dream was to build a film studio capable of producing world-class Chinese movies in Hong Kong. 
      Cut to Hong Kong, 1957: A young filmmaker named Run Run Shaw purchased 46 acres of land on a quiet hilltop in Clearwater Bay overlooking the South China Sea. His dream was to build a film studio capable of producing world-class Chinese movies in Hong Kong. 
      Cameras rolled in 1958 and over the next few years sound stages, production offices, editing suites, film processing, sound recording, dubbing rooms and even a staff dormitory all came ‚Äòonline‚Äô. By 1961, with 1,200 staff on board, Shaw Studios was the largest privately owned studio in the world. With an average turnover of 15 movies a year, and a record 26 in 1965, Shaw Brothers and Hong Kong cinema had entered a new golden age.
      
      The music from this era was different ‚Äì it was time of transition. Post war swing, the legacy of Shanghai, was gradually giving way to electric guitars and early rock ‚Äòn roll. The movie dialog and songs were still Mandarin ‚Äì pre dating the Canto-pop of today ‚Äì but the look was now big hair, high heels and mini skirts ‚Äì the 60s had arrived. 
      
      RETROCHINE is a celebration of this era, when the mood was shifting and the party was really getting started in Hong Kong, still Asia‚Äôs most cosmopolitan and fascinating city.
      
       THE SESSIONS
      Widgery & Wilson were given access to the original soundtracks from Shaw Brothers films and the theme for the album, ‚Äòa night out in Hong Kong‚Äô, emerged, inspired by the nightclub sequences in the movies. Widgery wrote in Canada, sending over initial tracks as they took shape, and Wilson invited artistes into Schtung‚Äôs Hong Kong studios to contribute. Associate Producer Tung Tang supervised recording sessions throughout 2007. 
      
      Key players were Allan Lau, Peng Fei & Johnny Yim - all composers and arrangers at the forefront of the new cosmopolitan Mando-Pop movement emanating from Hong Kong & Shanghai. They were later joined by vocalists Gloria Tang, Tina Chu & June Tang, up and coming ‚Äòindie divas‚Äô in the Chinese music scene. Chinese classical players Hou Shih Chieh and Ella Choi also added Erhu (Chinese violin) and Gu Zheng (Chinese harp).

title: Retrochine - Retrochine Vol. 1 (Ian Widgery & Morton Wilson)

description:
Snejl is back after a long time and is ready to deliver 4 tracks of catchy tech-house, techno, experimental, house‚Ä¶.hell, there is even some industrial touch in there! This time we do have something very different to offer, and the whole EP is entitled ‚Äì Night and Day coming from a very talented and actually very ‚Äú underground‚Äù artist, as his name says it all.
          All the tracks range from tribal rythms and drums, to deep basslines and percussive noises that will tease and surprise the listeners all the way through.
          This unbelievably jacking EP splits in the border between techno, house and experimental but at the same time comes with a very fresh and original approach to the overall sound right now. Don‚Äôt miss this one‚Ä¶
          
          
          Release date :20th of March 2009
title: Snejl007 - Paris Underground - Night and Day EP

description:
After the classically inspired, yet devilishly modern tech-house statements on his last E.P for Dessous, comes this too-hot-to-trot release from UK young blood Burnski.
  
  Building on the solid, no-nonsense aesthe- tics of his previous work he presents his unique vision of today‚Äòs club sound.
  
  Quite the picture of current hybrid trends, between old vs new, 'Draw Your Sword' infuses classic chicago jackin‚Äò beats with a soaring, building anthemic hook. The track builds insistently with a tough, pushing house Ô¨Çavour yet reminds us not to get too carried with a tense and teasing breakdown structure. Smart stuff that‚Äòll have you reaching for the rafters, in a moment of freshly spun dance music euphoria.
  
  'Sleep', on the Ô¨Çip side maintains Burnski‚Äòs clear love of the deep, jacking grooves of our american cousins, painting a vivid and bold picture of modern, teched-up soulful house music. An irresistible nu-jazz-house riff slides between the silkily sharp drum accents, building throughout and once again providing the danceÔ¨Çoor with some serious moments of tension and joyous resolve.
title: PF102 - Burnski, Draw Your Sword EP

description:
Songs are perhaps our most basic way of expression. When I was composing Inner|face I thought what a great experience it might be if some of my favourite artists could perform my own work. Globally considered, this is a hybrid piece of work, which exposes some of my inner exploits within music.

All in all, Inner|face has brought together an astonishing assortment of people, from the progressive Jos√© da Ponte to the Jazz vocal Maria Jo√£o. Among them, they cover a fair range of the contemporary music practiced in our time, from experimental electronic to classical Jazz and ethnic.

For me, their commonality is that they are an uncommonly talented group of musicians with such differences in their personal styles and in practical approach to music making, that you're ever likely to find working together. This makes me particularly proud of their collaboration and deeply grateful for their contribution to this record.

description:
My first release on Sole Music ( http://www.solemusic.co.uk ), home of Stevie Sole, Milton Jackson & Hiro to just name a few.
    Its also my first release since 2003, been away from producing music for a few years and "Satellites" was the first track i did when i started up again last year....so this is a very proud moment for me to be part of such a great label as Sole Music.
    Hope people will like these tracks as much as i do myself....
    
    Enjoy :D
    
    // chuck cogan

description: Longfellow Street's first EP offering of studio and live-in-the-studio recordings. Two songs by Mallory (Buckwild and Tall Grass), two songs by Trey (Honey and Traveler) and one song by Shawn (Sweet Em'ly Brown). Recorded in Trey's studio, multitracking our jams to capture the live feel of the bass and drums and whatever else worked from the live take, and overdubbing vocals and whatever else as necessary. Recorded with MOTU hardware and Logic.

description:
E‚Äô una canzone che parla del mondo delle Donne e del loro Amore nel senso piu‚Äô ampio del termine. 
Della parte ‚ÄúAndrogina‚Äù che ha in s√©
una donna qualsiasi di oggi,  nel ruolo sempre pi√π attivo e variegato che assume all‚Äôinterno della societ√†, a differenza di un tempo.
Del rapporto delle donne fra di loro, che pu√≤ essere di amicizia, di amore, di complicit√†, di condivisione di esperienze ecc.
Dei loro sentimenti, che le portano ad essere ed agire in determinati modi.
Donne che vivono situazioni di disagio, che combattono, hanno paura, non si lasciano andare.
Anche in questo brano (come spesso in altri miei lavori)  √® presente la costante degli occhi, che sono ‚Äúprofondi ed assorti‚Äù, 
come quelli di donne che osservano, scrutano, giudicano o semplicemente tacciono.
L‚Äôho intitolata ‚ÄúRitmo di Luna‚Äù anche per parlare dei ‚Äúritmi personali‚Äù di ciascuna donna, della volubilit√† della loro natura.
title: Ritmo di Luna

description: E‚Äô  un brano che parla di una qualsiasi donna che incontra un giorno la propria anima, uscita da lei stessa. Fra le due si crea un dialogo che tocca diversi temi, come quello che pu√≤ essere un senso di  solitudine che si prova  oggi e che porta ad avere diverse insicurezze, paure di ogni sorta.., perch√©, per esempio, la societ√†, non √® sicura sotto certi aspetti . E‚Äô un brano, se volete anche consolatorio, perch√©  esorta  a  non farsi prendere da queste paure, a cercare di amarci il pi√π possibile, a sentire ed affrontare quello che abbiamo dentro, anche se spesso pu√≤ essere doloroso;ad ammettere le nostre debolezze.di fronte a noi stessi  prima di tutto. Poi farlo; amarci, ‚Äúanche se non  possiamo‚Äù;‚Äùanche se non vogliamo‚Äù.
title: Anche Se Non Vuoi

description:
Music inspired by the 1957 film "The Admirable Crichton". An unwittingly insightful film, full of unintentional Kafka-esque poignancy (although the ending seems to contradict this), this album of partially improvised electronica reflects the atmosphere that I felt was half-hinted at, and largely glossed over by camp jokes and a terrible soundtrack.
      "Wrecked" is a interpretation of the initial inhuman silence of the shipwreck, something completely unseen in the actual film, that I feel compliments the anti-civilization (and to some degree anti-humanity) message that was borne half out of accident, half due to the nature of the story.
title: The Admirable Crichton

description:
digital-only re-release of the 1995 album.
  
 bernhard bockelbrink - guitars, basses, programming
  
 christian slawinger - keyboards
  
 the title for 'the mesh of a riddle' is taken from john brunner's 'the shockwave rider', the title 'red star, winter orbit' is taken from a short story written by william gibson and bruce sterling
  
 the track mass at dawn was also featured on the discordia compilation 5
  
 the original cd came with a 8 page booklet with photos of the polish artist pjot cyplik.

description: ‚ÄòLandshapers‚Äô is an oral history project which tells the story of the South Downs through the people who live and work there. A joint undertaking between the South Downs Joint Committee, Natural England and Hampshire County Council, the six audio visual files help explain how this landscape has been, and continues to be, shaped by man. These stories cover a wide range of themes intrinsically linked to the unique landscape we see today, all presented by a variety of local experts and accompanied by evocative and inspiring images of the South Downs. These are impassioned and personal accounts by the narrators based on their own background and experience. The audio files can also be downloaded onto mp3 players and are intended to accompany a number of walks in the South Downs where these themes are relevant. It is hoped these narratives will enhance your experience of the landscape as you explore it.
title: Landshapers - Voices from the South Downs

description:
In the year AD 802,701 humanity has evolved into two separate species: the Eloi and the Morlocks. The Eloi are the spoiled, attractive upper class, living in luxury on the surface of the earth while the Morlocks live underground, tending machinery and providing food, clothing and infrastructure for the Eloi. Each class evolved and degenerated from different social classes as humans, a theme that reflects upon H.G. Wells' sociopolitical opinions.
    
    The main difference from their earlier ruler-worker state is that while the Morlocks continue to support the world's infrastructure and serve the Eloi, the Eloi have undergone significant physical and mental deterioration. Having solved all problems which required strength, intelligence or virtue, they have slowly become dissolute, frail animals. While one initially has the impression that the Eloi live a life of play and toil less abundance, it is revealed that the Morlocks are tending to the Eloi's needs for the same reason a farmer tends to cattle - because the Eloi compose most (if not all) of the Morlocks diet and the Eloi are no longer capable of acting in any other role than to be eaten by the Morlocks.

TARON-TREKKA "Arb11 / Soon" [blues! 01]. "Finest killer Funk" according to De:Bug, and "solid start" for LittleWhiteEarbuds. Digital only release.

DE:BUG Review:
"Brut! has a new unexpected sublabel, blues!-y in its undertones."Soon" is a gentle acidic pumping House track for the deepest heads among us. Simple. And the string monster "Arb11" is the best Detroit school of the second generation in its third appearance - saying it for the mystics. What it is, is the finest killer Funk and needs to be honoured properly. So dear House DJs, you better trust this".
Bleed (May 2009)
http://de-bug.de/reviews/35666.html

Taron-Trekka's "Arb11" turns "Break Night" inside out; "Soon" articulates moody vibes w/knobby 303 groove. Solid start for Blues! label 7/10
(July 2009)

description:
Inevitable Hypocrisy is a concept album exploring the inner turmoil and turbulence of relationships and interdependence upon one another from multiple points of view. Featuring keyboard-driven rock with complex meters and soaring vocals, the two main characters espouse their (often conflicting) views on life and human interaction. The album includes a twenty-minute epic instrumental, Cloudmaker, which incorporates themes from the other tracks in a vein familiar to progressive rock fans and made popular by bands like Dream Theater, Yes, and Rush. The gritty, compelling, passion goes from furious, driving rhythms one minute to crystal-clear solo keyboard lines the next. Songs like ‚ÄúWelcome to The Oval‚Äù and ‚ÄúIgnite‚Äù show off the amazing technique of a classically-trained pianist.
  
  The album‚Äôs heartfelt lyrics raise questions about life, our place in society, and human interaction. It is easy to identify with the album‚Äôs characters and their struggles, as they are constantly forced to re-evaluate the placement of their trust, and in doing so experience longing, brooding anger, happiness, and ultimately acceptance and peace. Inevitable Hypocrisy covers a very wide emotional spectrum and makes heavy use of musical themes and modes to establish character moods. The characters‚Äô lives conform to patterns that are easy to relate to, yet the unique examples and situations encountered by the characters have caught many listeners off-guard.
  
  The album‚Äôs sound and instrumentation are truly unique. Featuring mellow pianos, vintage keyboards, driving drums, powerful synth leads and warm pads, it also makes use of instruments rarely-heard in progressive rock, including both sampled saxophone and violin solos as well as a Hammond Model A organ, spoken word, and other nontraditional samples. The wonderfully warm yet clear pianos include a Yamaha C7 grand and a Steinway K upright, providing a brilliantly-clear sound that can only result from well over a decade of piano performance experience.
  
  True to its progressive rock roots, Inevitable Hypocrisy showcases a complex writing style involving rapid key and meter changes, key-blazing solos that would make Jordan Rudess envious, recurring musical themes, unique chord structures, and tight lyrical/musical integration. Characters recycle melodies and lyrics from each other, demonstrating differing thoughts and perspectives on common issues. Themes recur throughout the album in different keys, modes, and meters, and tight integration of musical composition allows these rapid transitions to flow easily and naturally.
  
  Inevitable Hypocrisy provides a refreshing new sound that is accessible (most notably ‚ÄúReady For Tomorrow‚Äù and ‚ÄúLess‚Äù), yet incredibly deep and complex. It explores our inmost thoughts and is unafraid to say out loud the things we often only dare to think in our heads.
  
  Drew Crawford has just graduated high school, and is a classically-trained keyboardist and vocalist. He will be attending college in Longview, Texas and is looking for a band that can handle the complex, challenging music he wants to play. He enjoys composing music for short films and owns his own computer repair business. Drew is a three-year member of the Oklahoma All-State Choir, an honor granted to less than twenty graduating seniors statewide, and this is his first published album.
title: Inevitable Hypocrisy

description:
Dubfire ‚Äì ‚ÄúWicked E.P.!‚Äù
      
      Luciano ‚Äì ‚ÄúLove Monkey Skulls so will play it with my skulls to match a monkey!‚Äù
      
      Laurent Garnier ‚Äì ‚ÄúReally like this EP Will play a couple of tracks from it ‚Äì Monkey Skulls def a nice one!‚Äù
      
      Nic Fanciulli ‚Äì ‚ÄúLove what these guys are doing! Full support.‚Äù
      
      Cirillo (Circo Loco/ DC10) ‚Äì ‚ÄúVoodootribalanalogism!! Burra!‚Äù
      
      Danton Eeprom ‚Äì ‚ÄúVery consistent label led by two true music lovers. Once again I'm not disappointed, this one particular number has a festive edge without overdoing it. Digging it a lot. Thanks.‚Äù
      
      Carl Cox ‚Äì ‚ÄúGreat release! Jet Project can do no wrong at the moment.‚Äù
      
      X‚Äì Press 2 - ‚ÄúWow! Mighty grooves from Silicone Soul‚Äôs label. Jet Project absolutely kill it with these tracks. Big support from me.‚Äù
      
      TG ‚Äì ‚ÄúMonkey skulls is great! Lovely wobbly tune! Def support from me!‚Äù
      
      Darko Esser ‚Äì ‚ÄúSuper! Love this release, will play Monkey Skulls and Midnight Drumsticks. Very originally produced music. Darkroom Dubs is a great label!!‚Äù
      
      Silicone Soul's fantastic Darkroom Dubs label returns in swift fashion, fresh from the success of their current Sound Of Glasgow release that featured tracks from a couple of Scotland's most exciting new talents, Sei-A and Gary Beck.
      
      For this new release we hop across the water to the shores of Northern Ireland to catch up with DRD regulars the Jet Project. The Shine and Stiff Kitten residents, Timmy Stewart and John McIver are in the form of their lives right now. Previous releases on this label have shot them to the fore of the techno world, and with their current remix of Matt Playford's 'Analogue Tear' on Paul Woolford's Intimacy label doing well, and a stunning EP for Steve Lawler's Viva Music on the horizon, the guys trademark ass-kicking brand of techno is set to heard throughout 2009.
      
      Here they deliver a collection of their finest work to date on the 'Monkey Skulls E.P.' A melting pot of styles and influences, this four-track selection takes a major influence from the African continent, with traditional drums, vocals and percussion prominent in all. Yes there has been a host of releases with an ethnic flavour this season, but when they are as HEAVY as these, there is always room for more, in our record bags!
      
      This is a mighty EP, so handle with care! Watch out for the Monkeys!!
title: Jet Project - Monkey Skulls (Preview)

description:
iDJ Magazine  - "I never normally need much encouragement to break into a full-on pimp strut, but 'Mandan's got me making like the consummate Huggy Bear. Afrilounge manage to ramp up the funk even more, while 'Call It Deep' is a slab of prime house. Brilliant!"
    
    Raveline Magazine Germany - "Wonderful music...full support!"
    
    M.A.N.D.Y. - "Mandan kicks!"
    
    Agnes - "Raw killer!!!!"
    
    Laurent Garnier - "Nice trip will play it out!"
    
    Ben Watt - "Under the jungle canopy of thick lush tropical vegetation. Nice."
     
    Hector Romero - "Feeling the groove on Mandan - Can't wait to play it!"
     
    King Roc - "Call it Deep gets it right on the groove!"
    
    Hernan Cattaneo - "Proper house music both Mandan‚Äôs rock!"
     
    D'Julz - "Great E.P. Digging all the tracks!"  
    
    Solomun - "Great remix!!"
    
    Len Faki - "Yes, This is deep house with dubby twist at its best!"
    
    2000 and One - "Call It Deep. Deep jazzy and house stuff, totally up my alley:)."
    
    Ashley Beedle - "Top quality from Darkroom Dubs once again - Liapin has certainly rocked this house. Big support from me!"
    
    Sasse - "Great tools, rocks my floors! Will play!" 
    
    Milton Jackson - "Excellent stuff! All 3 are great."
    
    Karotte (Cocoon) - "Once again Liapin does an amazing house track. I love it!‚Äù
    
    Dennis Ferrer -‚ÄúMandan is very good!‚Äù
    
    
    Back in late 2008 I brought you a winter sampler from Silicone Soul's Darkroom Dubs label that featured a number of tracks from upcoming releases. One of them, 'Mandan' and without doubt the most popular of the package came from Richard Rotfu√ü... aka Liapin. 
    Liapin, together with Eduard Hartter and Markus Liefke aka Liefko, are German trio Afrilounge. 2002 saw them begin their journey together, but it was with their 2004 Get Physical release 'The Dude' that they really announced their arrival. The success of the release saw them rewarded with the task of remixing M.A.N.D.Y.'s seminal classic 'Body Language'. Together the trio have released and remixed for a number of labels, including the likes of Connaisseur, 8Bit, Playmate, Systematic and Poker Flat. 
    2008 has seen Liapin branching out and delivering killer cuts himself. Solo projects have come on Connaisseur, Genowefa and Connect Four and now, after bringing you the lead track on the winter sampler, I am happy to be able to bring you the full... Mandan E.P. 
    Title track 'Mandan' is a huge groove-fest. Dubby bassline, cheeky vocal sample and delicate tom-toms make for a wicked number that has already picked up a host of big name support from guys including, Laurent Garnier, Dennis Ferrer, Steve Bug, DJ Hell, Agnes, Charles Webster and many more... 
    So time for the new additions, and they really do not come much better. Teaming back up with his boys, Afrilounge take 'Mandan' even deeper with their 'Afrilounge In Your Soul Dub'. Dubbing things out further, with hints of Djembe drums and bubbling effects, this really is a smokers delight. Soulful to the end. 
    Rounding out the package is a real gem from Liapin. 'Call It Deep', as the title explains, does delve in that direction, yet has a demon kick, that takes hold. Infectiously locking on, this track will have you grinding your way across the floor with a gangsta'S swagger. Stunning! 
    Overall, I think you will be hard pushed to find a finer promo release in your inbox this weekend. Liapin and the Afrilounge boys are true masters of their craft.... Get down, and get funky!
title: Liapin - Mandan (Preview)

description:
Complex_City
                 
                Well, a further release by Crazy Language. This time Francisco 
                Godikinho from Portugal provides an insight to his kind of 
                complex_city of sound. 
                
                The album includes 17 songs and it is an amazing trip starting 
                at point zero pushing you from left to right and from top to down. 
                Some songs begin really calm and do not loose these wonderful 
                moods until the end where others break inside and wrench out 
                your personal mind drifts. The quality of Franciscos music is 
                amazing and you will find ambient songs, IDM abstractions and 
                four to the floor music. Consequently complex_city.   [dnn7]

description:
KM002
            
            This EP is about to clarify two things. First: &ME is still backing his obscure fondness for 
            syntax, funny additional characters and acronyms. So, the A-side is called ‚ÄúF.I.R.‚Äù (and 
            nobody knows, what it stands for. If you just read it as a word, it makes a cool sound, though. 
            Just as if you would get a ruler to vibrate and pull it over the desk), while the flip is entitled 
            ‚Äú+++‚Äù. 
            Second: it clarifies something about its creator. &ME is non of those bouncing show-offs that 
            would forget to play the next record in a club, just because he is so busy with pointing both 
            forefingers at himself all the time. &ME is the type of guy that would coproduce stuff for 
            Hell, Lotterboys/-girls or Terranova without really taking so much credit for it. We say: cut it! 
            Days of modesty are over. 
            ‚ÄúF.I.R.‚Äù is the essence of everything &ME stands for, a true and flawless peaktime-beauty. It 
            joins his intuition for stringency in structure, his sensibility for a sophisticated and safe walk 
            over the shaky bridge from House to Pop, the precision of laying out a track to be 
            unmistakably danceable, but not intrusive and last not least his ability to pitch a female vocal- 
            sample to let it sound like a Rick Astley-outtake. Safe to say, that this might be his sweetest 
            work so far. 
            ‚Äú+++‚Äù on the other hand appears to be some tricky chicanery. It starts like a lot of B-sides 
            start, as a reduced space for little reflexive experiments, or however it is whitewashed when a 
            track just isn‚Äôt that spectacular. But then, there is a kickdrum-monster arising out of this housy 
            self reflection, a monster, that grabs some percussions and vocalsamples as companions and 
            culminates into a massive break, thfor sure no pending questions.
title: &ME - KM002 - F.I.R. / +++

description:
Chinwag Live: Mobile Metamorphosis was recorded on Mon, 26th Feb 2007 in London.

Mobile business models are starting to shift, and with them the mobile value chain. How will these changes grow the mobile market and who will benefit? Will 2007 be the tipping point?

The panel included Hugh Griffiths, representing O2, Jessica Sandin, Senior Consultant and Head of Mobile Practice at Fathom Partners, Jonathan MacDonald, Sales Director at Blyk, Russell Buckley, Managing Director of AdMob Europe and was chaired by Tim Green, Executive Editor of Mobile Entertainment Magazine.

The podcast was sponsored by CBS Interactive. The event was produced for Chinwag by Deirdre Molloy.

For more information, see: http://live.chinwag.com/mobilemetamorphosis
tag_list: "chinwag live" advertising debate london mobile business
title: Chinwag Live: Mobile Metamorphosis

description:
Directly from klubbsoulmates.blogspot.com:

Efter en otroligt rolig men utpumpande helg p√• streetstar i solnahallen, med mitt engagemang fr√§mst som tekniker och dj-ass, men √§ven fotograf, har jag √§ntligen orkat resa mig fr√•n s√§ngen f√∂r att kn√•pa ihop den h√§r mixen. Och jag kan annonsera att mic-sjukan nu √§r √∂ver. Jag k√§nner mig som en riktig selecta efter att ha greppat miccen och talat in de sm√• korta, men inte obetydliga meningarna om vad och vem och hur och var, och framf√∂rallt om l√•tarna!

Det √§r en hel del nytt, bla Mr.V - "Tales from the deepside" (!!), l√•tar fr√•n "Palmistry" p√• Osunlandes label Yoruba och inte minst Jay Tripwires "Afrocentric Urban Orchestra" - bomb som den √§r.

Andra timmen √§r dubbig och housedansv√§nlig, och allts√• ett sammandrag av l√•tar som jag h√∂rt under helgen p√• Streetstar framf√∂rallt under house-t√§vlingarna. description: The group Agents Del Futuro let me into their studio to capture some live recordings with the Zoom H4n handheld recorder. These test recordings alternate between 2-channel recordings using the H4n's built-in stereo microphones, and 3/4-channel recordings that combine the built-in mics with external line and mic sources routed into the H4n. None of the recordings have been doctored in post-production, except to add fades and adjust volume levels. My full review of the Zoom H4n will post on CNET.com 04/13/09.
title: Zoom H4n recordings

description:
First words
      
      recorded mostly under the supervision of Disk Jockey Staplegun apart from Igloo, where I was left to my own devices. Paddy Burton plays wonderful guitar for the last 9 minutes & 25 seconds of Bank Robbers From Space.
       
      Pie was recently played on Sound Art Radio 
      
      The covers started in New Zealand when I had my laptop & a cheap microphone, I made a terrible copy of Killing In The Name Of by Rage Against The Machine on Sony Acid Pro. this was just one track on the album 'First Draught' which I gave Disk Jockey Staplegun for christmas in 2008 & it was the only track he liked on the whole album, he wanted to do it better & on Logic Pro instead, so we did the White Stripes & the rest is history.
title: Sinister Dexter - First Words

description:
**UPDATE: In 2021 my Path of Souls series will be expanded into fiction books, featuring ancient mysteries, quantum technology and the race to discover the source of consciousness. Visit benjaminbrewis.com to sign up for updates**

Deep, dark and mysterious; The Path Of Souls takes you through the Egyptian 'Book Of The Dead' on a sonic journey of twists and tales. Featuring the haunting sounds of the likes of Future Sound Of London, The Orb, Leftfield, Banco De Gaia, Sasha, L.S.G. and Aphex Twin, these are sounds you have likely NEVER heard before.
    
One for the heart, the mind and the spirit, listen to all the mixes that have been created either using decks or sequenced in Sony Acid or Logic Pro. The first mix was created almost 20 years ago, with Part 10 due for release in late 2020.

Enjoy and immerse yourselves in the sounds.
tag_list: firesnake progressive ambient psychedelic deep egyptian mystical esoteric house breaks techno cinematic atmosphere
title: Firesnake - Path Of Souls - Mix Collection

description:
This anthology will feature various works that came out of Berklee class projects as well as general compositional or production experiments from 2008, 2009 and 2010, so the songs vary stylistically as it is not an "album" in the traditional sense. 
  I have a strong affinity for electronic composers such as Aphex Twin, Boards of Canada, Karlheinz Stockhausen and others that approached many of their works not as a "singles or album" mindset, but purely from an exploration, discovery and experimentation aspect. To either dive into something as a self education experience or to see how far something new could be pushed. This collection is the first of what I hope to be an ongoing series that contains works done in the same spirit.
title: Homework - Vol 1

description:
Cornflower's debut album, from his new record label Time is Art Records, is bursting with energy and potential. His fusion of world, funk, electro-pop, trance and beatbox with tinges of indigenous and aboriginal influences, makes for a deep listening experience. With his improvisational style, Cornflower's unique song structures and musical movements will surprise you as each passing beat and melody unfold before your ears.

The title track "Journey into Sound" is an invitation to the listener, communicating the ride that one is about to take while listening to the album. Then emerges "In the Moment", a jazzy, improvisational scat piece that is reminiscent of one of his main influences Bobby McFerrin. "Wizards & Witches" has a great hook that carries you as Cornflower repeats the sacred hierarchy of our lineal purpose. The songs "Heartshine" and "One Drop" are upbeat and emotive, while giving a glimpse deeper into the personal path that Cornflower is on. "Calling to Source" is the epic of the album, showing off his jam band and electronica musical roots, as he segways from a hip-hop rock groove into a classic drum & bass loop. Making a special appearance on the last track "Oceanwater" is guitar maestro Jeff Pevar, known for his time as lead guitarist for CPR, Marc Cohn, Jazz is Dead and Phil Lesh & Friends. Pevar's additions to Cornflower's ode to our precious oceans, brings a refreshing glimpse at what can happen when his voice is accompanied by multi instrumental layerings, that really showcases the true musicianship and potential of this new voice on the scene.

title: Journey into Sound

description:
Les Fleurs du Mal (named for the Baudelaire anthology, of course‚Äîbut you knew that) is a playful bit of minimal action, with a tick-tock rhythm, a synth-bass that burrows directly into the brain, and all manner of blips and bleeps to keep the tech-heads happy. It‚Äôs subtle, fun and extremely funky, all at the same time.
      
The remix duty is assigned to Naples-via-London Flavio Diaz, known for EPs on Analytic Trail, Loose Records and Weave Music. Flavio takes the weirdness and interpret it as a driving and condensed techno bomb, making that two out of two for Team Biatch.
title: Les Fleurs Du Mal

description: For most of n5MD's existence the "IDM" ( Intelligent Dance Music) genre descriptor has been used sparingly and only for those artists that utilize a more strict electronic pallet. We shy away from such a specific genre tag because, for the most part, the music created by our artists lacks the "D" of IDM...yes, dance. That trend changes with Another Electronic Musician's latest album "Five", Jase Rex's fifth release under the n5MD group of labels. Five puts the dance back into Intelligent Dance Music through the fusion of Techno, House, Electro, and Jazz with Rex's now signature sculpted sound. He has created something unique while leaving the genre's subtler signposts intact to lead the way. "Five" pushes and pulls you to where IDM used to before it went astray with its over the top cuts and glitch and puts the focus back in the mind and hips.
tag_list: Another Electronic Musician n5MD IDM Dub Glitch House Ambient Electronica
title: Five

description:
Sensation Level
            
This new release from Crazy-Language comes this time from Lyon, France. Romain Roqueta, know in the digital world as Sukdabeat presents us with a delightful record filled with pleasant electronic glockenspiels, warm synths pulled from various hardware material and tight hip-hopish beats reminiscent of some of the best and respected electronic artists around (e.g. Chris Clark). Struktur introduces us to the complex world that goes on Sukdabeat‚Äôs mind: the beats have an amazing attention to detail and will get you hooked right from the start; clicks, plops, distant bugs, multi-layered kicks and snares are the structure of these eight tracks. It feels as if we had just landed on a distant alien planet, but at the same time, this strange place felt strangely familiar to us. This is where the melodies pop in: immediate synths, pleasant sines, music-boxes, all of them rich, heart-felt and very accessible creating a curious fight between melody and beat [man/machine?], where both contestants win, to your own delight.
            
Once you start exploring deeply inside this planet, you won‚Äôt ever want to leave. You‚Äôll find your new home here. [F.G.]
tag_list: sukdabeat "crazy language" idm electro electronic netaudio
title: cl-022 | Sukdabeat - Struktur
